        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;└── pages/</td>
            <td>Folder</td>
            <td>Page routes (Emergency dashboard, incident files, safety tips).</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<hr/>

<h2>🔄 Core Application Flows</h2>

<h3>1. User Authentication Flow</h3>
<p>Illustrates the login/registration sequence. If Supabase is unavailable or keys are missing, the system transparently falls back to LocalStorage Mock Auth, ensuring the app remains browsable offline.</p>

<div class="diagram">
<pre>
User                      React Frontend (AuthContext)      Supabase / LocalStorage
 │                                     │                               │
 ├─1. Submit Sign-In Form ────────────►│                               │
 │                                     ├─2. Is Supabase configured?───►│
 │                                     │                               │
 │                                     ├───► Yes: Authenticate URL ───►│
 │                                     │     & retrieve Session        │
 │                                     │                               │
 │                                     └───► No: Fallback to Local ───►│
 │                                           Storage Mock Database     │
 ◄─3. Active User Session Loaded ──────┤                               │
</pre>
</div>

<h3>2. Emergency SOS Alert Flow</h3>
<p>When the user triggers the SOS button, the system plays a synthesized alarm and broadcasts location coordinate payloads to the server database.</p>

<div class="diagram">
<pre>
 [User triggers SOS Button]
            │
            ├─► Play synthesized alarm siren in browser (Web Audio API)
            │
            ├─► Capture GPS Coordinates (HTML5 Geolocation API)
            │         │
            │         ├─► Success: Attach GPS coordinates (lat, lon)
            │         └─► Denied/Fail: Attach "Location Unavailable"
            │
            ▼
    { Check Connection }
            │
            ├─► Connected: POST SOS payload to Supabase 'sos_alerts' table
            └─► Offline: Push alert payload to InMemory fallback list
            │
            ▼
   [Broadcast Alert to Trusted contacts circle]
</pre>
</div>

<h3>3. Incident Reporting Flow</h3>
<p>Filing an incident report manages both unstructured text data and evidence media. Media files are uploaded to object storage, and the resulting public URL is stored in the database.</p>

<div class="diagram">
<pre>
   [User files Incident Report]
                │
         { Selected image? }
          /           \
       Yes             No
        │               │
  { Storage active? }   │
    /       \           │
  Yes        No         │
   │          │         │
 Upload to  Convert to  │
  Storage   Base64 text │
   │          │         │
   └─────┬────┘         │
         ▼              │
    [Build Payload]◄────┘
         │
    { DB Active? }
      /        \
   Yes          No
    │            │
 Write to     Write to
Supabase Table Mock Array
</pre>
</div>

<hr/>

<h2>🔒 Row-Level Security (RLS) Policy Blueprint</h2>
<p>To protect users' sensitive safety data, the database uses PostgreSQL RLS. Below is a blueprint of how access is regulated:</p>

<table>
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Table</th>
            <th>Policy Name</th>
            <th>Operation</th>
            <th>Logic / Permission</th>
            <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>trusted_contacts</strong></td>
            <td>Users can manage their own contacts</td>
            <td>ALL</td>
            <td>USING (true)</td>
            <td>Allows users to query and alter contacts.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>sos_alerts</strong></td>
            <td>Anyone can file an SOS alert</td>
            <td>INSERT</td>
            <td>WITH CHECK (true)</td>
            <td>Permits quick reporting during emergencies.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>sos_alerts</strong></td>
            <td>Anyone can read SOS alerts</td>
            <td>SELECT</td>
            <td>USING (true)</td>
            <td>Enables safety dashboards to list current reports.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>incident_reports</strong></td>
            <td>Anyone can file incident reports</td>
            <td>INSERT</td>
            <td>WITH CHECK (true)</td>
            <td>Allows rapid incident filing.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>incident_reports</strong></td>
            <td>Anyone can read incident reports</td>
            <td>SELECT</td>
            <td>USING (true)</td>
            <td>Allows public mapping of unsafe zones.</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

</body>
</html>
